{
  "texts": [
    "Remark 5.4.",
    "If we accepted the claim in [Moc15, Theorem 1.11] that the absolute Galois group of any Kummer-faithful field of characteristic zero is slim (i.e., every open subgroup has trivial center), then the field K(σ) would not be Kummer-faithful for any σ ∈ G K since the absolute Galois group G K(σ) of K(σ) is abelian; G K(σ) is the closed subgroup ⟨σ⟩ in G K generated by σ.",
    "However, Mochizuki recently informed us that there is a gap in the proof of this claim and the status remains open for general Kummer-faithful fields of characteristic zero.",
    "If the Kummer-faithfulness result for K(σ) holds when e = 1, then it leads us to conclude that the above claim does not hold in the general case, although it provides no explicit counterexample.",
    "It would also answer in the negative the questions [MT22, Remark 2.4.1, Questions 1 and 2] posed by Minamide and Tsujimura, which ask whether the absolute Galois group of any torally Kummer-faithful field is slim."
  ]
}